    <fr:title text="Solutions to Horn clauses">Solutions to Horn clauses</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Quiz</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Consider the following set of Horn clauses:
</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {align}
    x = 1 &\to  p(x) \\
    p(x) \land  x' = x + 1 &\to  p(x') \\
    p(x) &\to  0 \leq  x
  \end {align}
]]></fr:tex><html:p>
  Answer the following questions:
</html:p><html:ol><html:li>
    Is the following a solution to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \Sigma  \triangleq  \{p \to  x = 1\}
    ]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li>
    What about 
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \Sigma  \triangleq  \{p \to  x \geq  1\}
    ]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
  
    
    
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Solution</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:ol><html:li>
      Substituting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = 1]]></fr:tex> we get
      <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
        \begin {align}
          x = 1 &\to  x = 1 \\
          x = 1 \land  x' = x + 1 &\to  x' = 1 \\
          x = 1 &\to  0 \leq  x
        \end {align}
      ]]></fr:tex>
      clearly the first clause is satisfied, but in the second clause obviously <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x']]></fr:tex> should be 2 thus this is false.
    </html:li>
    <html:li>
      again substituting in the formula we get
      <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
        \begin {align}
        x \geq  1 &\to  x = 1
        x \geq  1 &\to  x' = x + 1 &\to  x' \geq  1
        x \geq  1 &\to  0 \leq  x
        \end {align}
      ]]></fr:tex>
      for the case of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = 1]]></fr:tex> we can satisfy the first clause, the second clause is also satisfied by the fact that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x']]></fr:tex> can be &gt; 1, finally the third clause is just trivially satisfied. Thus, we have that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma  \vDash  \mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> as we have demonstrated that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  C \in  \mathcal  C.\ \Sigma  \vDash  C]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li></html:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  
